# ============================================================
# TRADE CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: trade
scope: trade.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for trade.

## policy_rules
Trade policy constrains:
- who may propose trade
- who may approve trade
- what may be exchanged
- what may be disclosed publicly
- what must be reviewed or denied

## required_behavior
- party eligibility must be explicit
- exchange eligibility must be explicit
- approval gating must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public trade summary
- party-scoped trade detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow proposal only for valid parties
- allow approval only for valid authority
- allow bounded disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden exchange widening
- deny invalid or prohibited trade scope

## escalation_rules
If party identity,
trade scope,
approval authority,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the trade path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- party policy is explicit
- approval policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
